modules.description: This module provides functions to parse date, time, and datetime strings (or lex buffers) into UTC timestamps, with some returning optional timezone offsets, and formats timestamps into string representations using specific date-time formats. It operates on floats (timestamps) and tuples of (float * float) to handle timezone information, supporting use cases like converting user-inputted date-time strings to standardized UTC values or generating human-readable datetime outputs with timezone context. Specialized functions manage partial datetime parsing and timezone-aware conversions, ensuring flexibility in handling ambiguous or timezone-specific data.

parses and formats date-time strings into UTC timestamps, handling timezone offsets through float-based representations and tuples, with support for partial parsing and timezone-aware conversions. It operates on timestamps, date-time tuples, and lex buffers, enabling tasks like converting user input to standardized UTC values or generating formatted outputs with timezone context. Functions include parsing date, time, and datetime strings, as well as formatting timestamps into structured string representations. Examples include converting "2023-04-05T12:30:00Z" to a UTC timestamp or formatting a timestamp with a specific timezone offset.
